    "created_at": "2016-07-18T19:11:12Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-07-18T19:11:12Z",
    "body": "This may not be applicable to your use case, @cicithesquirrel, but [in my Atom package](https://github.com/lexicalunit/multi-wrap-guide/blob/master/lib/multi-wrap-guide.coffee#L137) the way I worked around this was to call `dispose()` rather than `clear()` on the menu I wanted to update. Then I add the new menu items just like you're doing. I probably would have used `clear()` though had I known it existed. Would be nice to get `clear()` documented if it's the intended solution for this kind of situation.\n"
