    "created_at": "2016-12-16T11:39:37Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-12-16T11:39:37Z",
    "body": "Not sure if it's the best solution, but I managed to do it the \"dirty\" way. \r\n\r\nBasically, I sent a message to `ipcMain` from `ipcRenderer` to \"rebuild\" the menu using the initial template. So whenever I add things to the menus and want to go back to the starting template I simply send a message to `ipcMain`.\r\n\r\nIt's not ideal, but at least it's something (since .clear() didn't really work):\r\n\r\nFrom renderer:\r\n```js \r\nipcRenderer.sendSync('rebuild-menu');\r\n```\r\n\r\nAt main process:\r\n```js\r\n// cachedTemplate is the initial template used when bootstrapping the application\r\n\r\nipcMain.on('rebuild-menu', (event, arg) => {\r\n  let resetMenu = Menu.buildFromTemplate(cachedTemplate);\r\n  Menu.setApplicationMenu(resetMenu);\r\n  event.returnValue = 'Rebuilt electron menu.';\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nNOTE that if you don't provide a `returnValue`,  the application halts.\r\n\r\nI know it's not ideal, but since there's no official and documented way of removing things from Menu, I had to basically reset the whole thing on demand."
  },
